        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 6:19PM PDT by NWS Reno NV</headline>
        <description>At 619 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Smith, or 18 miles northeast of Topaz Lake, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Smith, Smith Valley, and Artesia Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
